Oklahoma State Beats Harvard 71-54 in First Round of Basketball's NIT

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-03-16T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/oklahoma-state-beats-harvard-71-54-in-first-round-of-basketball-s-nit.html
  Oklahoma  State University defeated
Harvard University 71-54 in the first round of college
basketball’s National Invitation Tournament.  Oklahoma State advanced to play the winner of today’s round
one game between Washington State (19-12) and Long Beach State
(22-12).  Marshall Moses scored 18 points, Reger Dowell had 15 and
Matt Pilgrim added 12 for the Cowboys (20-13, 6-10 Big 12) at
Gallagher-Iba Arena in Stillwater, Oklahoma.  Kyle Casey led the Crimson (23-7, 12-2 Ivy) with 13 points
followed by Keith Wright and Laurent Rivard, who each had 10
points.  Harvard, which claimed a share of the Ivy League title for
the first time with  Princeton University , lost its bid for a
berth in the National Collegiate Athletic Association tournament
in A 63-62 playoff loss to the Tigers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  